piupiu
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:in traditional Maori dress, a skirt made of a fringe of dried flax leaves attached to a waistband.
Origin:Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
